div.div:
We choose to always move each raw Datum from disk into an Arc.
Disadvantages
:
This is wasteful b/c data read from SSTables are guaranteed to be used by exactly one thread.
One Arc costs 2 more usizes compared to a Box.
Each access requires an extra ptr hop. (Relevant mostly for the otherwise stack-only type of Datum::I64)
Modifying Arc's atomic counter would introduce memory barriers. But, iff we ensure to never clone() the Arc and instead always move it, we can prevent this cost.
Advantages
:
We reduce the variety of types.
The merged iterator item type is:
Without unifying types using Arc:
either `(&A, &B)` or `Result<(C, D)>`, for generic A,B,C,D.
With the unification:
either `(&K, &V)` or `Result<(K, V)>`, for generic K,V.
